---
source: bin/phoneme/tests/snapshots.rs
expression: stdout
---
Phoneme CLI

Usage: phoneme.exe [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  record            Push-to-talk: read stdin until EOF / Enter, then stop
  meeting           Meeting Mode: record mic + system audio as two linked recordings
  import            Import a local audio file (wav/mp3/m4a/flac) — or an http(s) URL (e.g. a YouTube link, downloaded via yt-dlp) — and transcribe it
  list              List recordings
  show              Show one recording
  retranscribe      Re-transcribe a saved recording
  cleanup           Re-run only the LLM cleanup step on a stored transcript
  summarize         Generate (or regenerate) an LLM summary of a recording
  suggest-tags      Re-run the LLM tag-suggestion step on a recording on demand
  suggest-entities  Re-run the LLM entity-extraction step on a recording on demand
  chapters          Generate a recording's topic chapters (or view stored ones with --show)
  notes             Get or set a recording's free-form notes
  edit              Edit a recording's transcript and/or metadata (title, favorite)
  find-replace      Find-and-replace literal text across a recording's transcript
  clip              Export a time range of a recording's audio to a new WAV
  speaker           Rename or clear a recording's diarized speaker labels
  search            Semantic (embedding) search over transcripts
  ask               Ask a question answered from your own transcripts, with citations (local RAG over the same hybrid retriever as `search`)
  reembed           Clear all embeddings and re-embed the whole library with the current model
  queue             Inspect and manage the transcription queue
  dictation         Re-grab a recent in-place dictation (the opt-in history)
  refire-hook       Re-fire the post-processing hook on a recording's stored transcript
  delete            Delete a recording
  doctor            Health check
  config            Configuration management
  daemon            Daemon control
  watch             Subscribe to the daemon's event stream
  hook              Test the configured hook
  tag               Manage recording tags
  entities          List the extracted entities across the library (the cross-recording entity facet: people, orgs, topics, terms — each with a recording count)
  profile           Manage config profiles (named full-config snapshots)
  export            Export all recordings and metadata to a zip file
  import-backup     Restore recordings + audio from a backup zip (the inverse of `export`)
  completions       Print a shell-completion script for the given shell to stdout
  version           Print version + commit info
  help              Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --no-color  Disable colored output (or set NO_COLOR=1)
      --json      JSON-lines output where supported
  -v, --verbose   Verbose tracing to stderr
  -h, --help      Print help
  -V, --version   Print version
